# Button Styling Guidelines for Monity

## Core Button Design Principle

**DEFAULT BUTTON STYLE**: All buttons in the Monity application must have **WHITE TEXT** with **NO BACKGROUND COLOR** (transparent background) and **NO BORDERS**.

## Standard Button Styling

### Primary/Default Buttons
```jsx
// Correct ✅
<button className="text-white hover:text-[#01C38D] transition-colors">
  Button Text
</button>

<button className="text-white hover:text-[#01C38D] px-4 py-2 rounded-lg transition-colors">
  Button Text
</button>

// WRONG ❌ - Never use backgrounds, borders, or dark text
<button className="bg-white text-black">Button Text</button>
<button className="bg-[#E8F0FE] text-gray-900">Button Text</button>
<button className="text-white border border-white">Button Text</button>
```

### Accent/Action Buttons (For Critical Actions Only)
Only use colored backgrounds for primary actions like:
- Form submissions (Sign Up, Login, Save, Update)
- Primary CTAs (Upgrade Now, Get Started)
- Confirmation actions

```jsx
// Correct ✅ - For primary actions only
<button className="bg-[#01C38D] text-white px-6 py-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#00b37e] transition-colors">
  Submit
</button>

<button className="bg-gradient-to-r from-[#01C38D] to-[#01C38D]/80 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl hover:from-[#01C38D]/90 hover:to-[#01C38D]/70 transition-all">
  Sign Up
</button>
```

### Danger/Destructive Buttons
```jsx
// Correct ✅ - Simple text button
<button className="text-red-400 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg hover:text-red-300 transition-colors">
  Delete
</button>

// Or with background for critical destructive actions
<button className="bg-red-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-red-700 transition-colors">
  Delete Account
</button>
```

### Icon Buttons
```jsx
// Correct ✅
<button className="text-white hover:text-[#01C38D] transition-colors p-2 rounded-lg">
  <svg className="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
    {/* icon path */}
  </svg>
</button>
```

### Navigation/Tab Buttons
```jsx
// Correct ✅
<button className={`text-gray-400 hover:text-white px-3 py-2 rounded-lg transition-all ${
  isActive ? 'text-white bg-[#262626]' : ''
}`}>
  Tab Name
</button>
```

## Common Patterns

### Standard Button Classes
```
text-white                          // Default text color
hover:text-[#01C38D]               // Hover state (color change)
hover:opacity-80                   // Alternative hover effect
transition-colors                   // Smooth transitions
px-4 py-2                          // Standard padding
rounded-lg                         // Rounded corners
```

### Button Sizing
```
Small:  px-3 py-1.5 text-sm
Medium: px-4 py-2 text-base
Large:  px-6 py-3 text-lg
```

## What NOT to Do

### ❌ NEVER Use These Patterns
```jsx
// White/light backgrounds with dark text
<button className="bg-white text-black">...</button>
<button className="bg-[#E8F0FE] text-gray-900">...</button>
<button className="bg-gray-100 text-gray-800">...</button>

// Borders on buttons
<button className="border border-white">...</button>
<button className="border border-gray-300">...</button>
<button className="border border-[#01C38D]">...</button>

// Light backgrounds in any form
<button className="bg-blue-100">...</button>
<button className="bg-green-50">...</button>
```

### ❌ NEVER Use These Classes on Buttons
- `bg-white`
- `bg-[#E8F0FE]`
- `bg-gray-100`, `bg-gray-200`, etc.
- `text-black`
- `text-gray-900`, `text-gray-800`
- `border`, `border-white`, `border-gray-*`, etc.
- Any light background color
- Any border classes

## Exception: Form Inputs
Note: This rule applies to **BUTTONS ONLY**. Form inputs (text inputs, textareas, selects) can have borders and different styling as needed for usability.

## Badge/Label Exception
Small status badges and labels (not interactive buttons) may use different styling:
```jsx
// Badges can have colored backgrounds and borders
<span className="bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm border border-yellow-300">
  PREMIUM
</span>
```

## Migration Checklist

When updating existing buttons:
1. ✅ Remove any `bg-white`, `bg-[#E8F0FE]`, or light background classes
2. ✅ Remove ALL `border` classes from buttons
3. ✅ Change `text-black` or `text-gray-900` to `text-white`
4. ✅ Add hover states with `hover:text-[#01C38D]` or `hover:opacity-80`
5. ✅ Keep transition classes for smooth interactions
6. ✅ Only use `bg-[#01C38D]` for primary action buttons

## Summary

**Golden Rule**: By default, all buttons should be:
- ✅ White text (`text-white`)
- ✅ No background (transparent)
- ✅ No borders
- ✅ Only hover effects (color change or opacity)

**Exception**: Only primary action buttons can have colored backgrounds like `bg-[#01C38D]`.

This ensures consistency across the entire Monity application and maintains the modern, clean aesthetic of the dark theme.
